**Respiration: the process of breaking down of food and relaese energy in the form of ATP is known as respiration:
Breathing vs respiration:
| **Feature**               | **Breathing**                                                               | **Respiration**                                                             |
| ------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **1. Definition**         | The **physical process** of taking in oxygen and giving out carbon dioxide. | The **chemical process** of breaking down food (glucose) to release energy. |
| **2. Type of process**    | **Physical / mechanical process**                                           | **Biochemical process**                                                     |
| **3. Where it occurs**    | Takes place in the **lungs** (in humans).                                   | Takes place in the **cells** of the body (in mitochondria).                 |
| **4. Energy involvement** | **No energy is released**, it only helps in gas exchange.                   | **Energy (ATP)** is released during respiration.                            |
| **5. Purpose**            | To **supply oxygen** to the body and **remove carbon dioxide**.             | To **produce energy** needed for body functions from food.                  |

| **Feature**               | **Aerobic Respiration**                              | **Anaerobic Respiration**                                               |
| ------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **1. Oxygen requirement** | Occurs **in the presence of oxygen (Oâ‚‚)**            | Occurs **in the absence of oxygen (Oâ‚‚)**                                |
| **2. End products**       | **Carbon dioxide (COâ‚‚)** and **water (Hâ‚‚O)**         | **Lactic acid** (in animals) or **alcohol + COâ‚‚** (in yeast)            |
| **3. Energy released**    | **More energy** is released (about 38 ATP molecules) | **Less energy** is released (about 2 ATP molecules)                     |
| **4. Site in cell**       | Occurs in the **mitochondria**                       | Occurs in the **cytoplasm**                                             |
| **5. Example**            | Humans, most animals, and plants                     | Yeast (during fermentation) and human muscles during **heavy exercise** |

